Package net.ssehub.comani.data

Interface IAnalysisQueue

All Known Implementing Classes:
CommitQueue
public interface IAnalysisQueue
This interface declares the methods a CommitQueue has to implement for its use by a commit analysis.
Author:
Christian Kroeher

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    Commit getCommit()
    Returns the first Commit in the queue if its status is CommitQueue.QueueState.OPEN.
    boolean isOpen()
    Returns whether this queue is open (true) or not (false).

  • Method Details

    • isOpen

      boolean isOpen()
      Returns whether this queue is open (true) or not (false). This method should be used in combination with the getCommit() method in order to check whether obtaining commits from this queue is possible as only open queues will provide commits. Further, only checking for non-null returns from the getCommit() method is not enough as extraction of commits may take longer than analyzing them. Hence, a proposed combination of usage is: 
       
 while(queue.isOpen()) {
     Commit commit = queue.getCommit();
     if (commit != null) {
         // Do something with the commit
     }
 }
      Returns:
      true if this queue is open and will provide commits; false otherwise

    • getCommit

      Commit getCommit()
      Returns the first Commit in the queue if its status is CommitQueue.QueueState.OPEN. If the queue has a different status or there are currently no commits available, this method will return null. However, returning null does not indicate that there are nor further commits extracted. See isOpen() for more information.
      Returns:
      the first commit in this queue or null if the queue is not open or no commit is available
